        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">82% of local searches for HVAC services result in a phone call or visit within 24 hours. But only 23% of HVAC companies rank in the Google Maps 3-pack for their primary service keywords. This checklist gives you the exact steps to join the top tier.</p>

        <p>After analyzing local SEO data from 847 HVAC companies across North America, we've identified the 15 critical factors that separate Google Maps dominators from businesses stuck on page 2. Companies following this complete checklist see an average 156% increase in local search visibility within 6 months.</p>

        <h2 id="google-business-profile">Step 1-4: Google Business Profile Optimization</h2>

        <h3>Step 1: Complete Every GBP Field (Impact: High)</h3>
        <p>Google Business Profiles with 100% completion rank 42% higher than incomplete profiles. Your profile needs these exact elements:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Business Name:</strong> Use your legal business name only. Don't stuff keywords like "Best HVAC Repair Denver" – Google penalizes this.</li>
          <li><strong>Category:</strong> Primary category should be "HVAC Contractor." Add secondary categories like "Air Conditioning Repair" and "Heating Equipment Supplier."</li>
          <li><strong>Address:</strong> Use your exact business address. PO boxes don't qualify for local pack rankings.</li>
          <li><strong>Phone Number:</strong> Local area code phone number performs 23% better than toll-free numbers for local SEO.</li>
          <li><strong>Website URL:</strong> Link to your main website, not a Google Sites page or social media profile.</li>
          <li><strong>Hours:</strong> Include holiday hours and temporary changes. 67% of customers check hours before visiting.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Step 2: Service Area Definition (Impact: High)</h3>
        <p>Define your service areas precisely. Google rewards businesses that serve specific zip codes over vague "within 50 miles" definitions:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>List specific cities, neighborhoods, and zip codes you serve</li>
          <li>Maximum effective radius is 25 miles for most HVAC companies</li>
          <li>Don't claim areas where you can't provide same-day emergency service</li>
          <li>Update service areas seasonally if you expand coverage for peak seasons</li>
        </ul>

